BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Author Event with Randal M. Jelks
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260407T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260407T190000
UID:ai1ec-147837-94576@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Author and IU professor Randal Maurice Jelks celebrates the re
 lease of his new book\,My America: Langston Hughes on Democracy.ABOUT THE 
 BOOK:My America traces Hughes’s journey from a child captivated by the w
 onder of Kansas City to cosmopolitan witness in Paris\, New York\, Mexico 
 City\, and Madrid. Langston Hughes is one of the few American writers who 
 consistently wrote about democracy from a joyous perspective\, and My Amer
 ica explores how his works speak to the political anxieties and crises we 
 face today.
LOCATION:Morgenstern Books & Cafe\, 849 South Auto Mall Road\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/author-event-with-randal-m-jelks/?instance_id=9
 4576
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Community Kundalini Yoga
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260407T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260407T193000
UID:ai1ec-147048-94233@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:We’ll follow Jai Dev in a pre-recorded class projected on a 
 large-screen in our studio. There is occasionally some lecture at the star
 t of class. Then we get into the movements and meditations to feel the tea
 chings.
